Combine broth, curry powder and salt in medium saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Stir in couscous, raisins and ginger; cover. Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes. Uncover; fluff with fork. Cool. Mix mayonnaise and lemon juice in large bowl until well blended. Add turkey, celery, onions and almonds; mix well. Add couscous mixture, oranges, grapes and parsley; mix lightly. Cover. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours, or until chilled.